div.p:
Signature
static void write_be64(uint8_t *buf, uint64_t val)
Purpose
writes val to buf[0..7] in big-endian byte order
using explicit shift-and-mask — NOT memcpy
Why NOT memcpy
on x86 (little-endian) memcpy of uint64_t reverses bytes;
0x0000000000000018 → 18 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 (wrong)
explicit shifts produce 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 18 (correct)
Implementation
buf[0] = val >> 56;  buf[1] = val >> 48;
buf[2] = val >> 40;  buf[3] = val >> 32;
buf[4] = val >> 24;  buf[5] = val >> 16;
buf[6] = val >>  8;  buf[7] = val >>  0;
